## Sales Checks (2-4 times per day)

### 1. Pipeline Review
- [ ] Review active deals and their status
- [ ] Identify deals needing attention or follow-up
- [ ] Check for any stalled opportunities

### 2. Follow-up Schedule
- [ ] Review scheduled follow-ups for the day
- [ ] Check for overdue follow-ups
- [ ] Update follow-up reminders as needed

### 3. Performance Metrics
- [ ] Check pipeline value and coverage
- [ ] Review win rate and conversion metrics
- [ ] Flag any significant deviations from targets

### 4. New Opportunities
- [ ] Review new leads or inquiries
- [ ] Qualify new prospects
- [ ] Add qualified leads to pipeline

---

## When to Reach Out

**Urgent (Immediate):**
- Major deal at risk of being lost
- Prospect escalation or serious complaint
- Competitive threat requiring immediate response
- Pricing or terms approval needed to close deal

**Important (Within 4 hours):**
- Follow-up needed on hot prospect
- Deal stalled requiring strategy adjustment
- New high-value opportunity to qualify
- Competitive intelligence requiring response

**Routine (Next heartbeat):**
- Regular pipeline review
- Standard follow-up activities
- Performance reporting
- Market trend monitoring

---

## When to Stay Quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK)

- No urgent deal issues
- No pending follow-ups due
- Nothing significant since last check
- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless critical

